# Supabase Configuration
# ----------------------

# 1. Project URL
# The base API URL for your Supabase project.
# Format: https://<project_id>.supabase.co
# Where <project_id> is the 20-character string (e.g., nlucbgajcftcnzjqcavn).
# Ensure there are no trailing slashes.
SUPABASE_URL=https://nlucbgajcftcnzjqcavn.supabase.co

# 2. Anonymous Key (Public)
# The "anon" key is safe to expose in client-side code (browsers, mobile apps).
# It allows unauthenticated access subject to your RLS (Row Level Security) policies.
# Format: A long JWT string starting with 'ey...'
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=sb_publishable_ONmVzK26KPvSfs8pAny2cQ_RyT6rofG

# 3. Service Role Key (SECRET - Do NOT Commit Real Value)
# This key bypasses RLS. strictly for backend/admin tasks.
# Jules/Agents should NOT need this for general development.
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your_service_role_key_here
